DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
"PGgraders.pl"
);


$b = random(5,7,1);
$a = random($b+1,12,1);
$c = random(7,11,1);


TEXT(&beginproblem);
BEGIN_TEXT
What is the longest pipe which can be maneuvered around a corner
joining a $a foot wide corridor and a $b foot wide corridor? Assume
that the pipe must be held horizontally throughout the maneuver, and ignore
the diameter of the pipe in your calculation.
$BR

\setlength{\unitlength}{0.5in}
\begin{picture}(5,3)
\thicklines
\put(0,0){\line(0,1){3}}
\put(2,0){\line(0,1){2}}
\put(0,3){\line(1,0){5}}
\put(2,2){\line(1,0){3}}
\put(0,1){\line(2,1){4}}
\thinlines
\put(1,1){\vector(1,0){1}}
\put(1,1){\vector(-1,0){1}}
\put(4,2.5){\vector(0,1){.5}}
\put(4,2.5){\vector(0,-1){.5}}
\put(2.6,2.1){\(t\)}
\put(1,1.6){\(u\)}
\put(3,2.6){\(v\)}
\put(.9,.7){$a}
\put(4.1,2.4){$b}
\end{picture}

To solve this problem we need to find the critical number for
the following function of the angle \(t\) shown in the picture
above
$BR
\{ans_rule(40)\}
$BR
Note: WeBWorK ONLY recognizes the following trig functions \(\sin()\),\(\cos()\),
\(\tan()\) and \(\sec()\).
$BR
The critical number occurs when
$BR
\(\tan(t)=\) \{ans_rule(30)\}
$BR
This critical number is a \{ans_rule()\} (Write MAX or MIN.)
$BR
Thus the maximal length of pipe which will fit is:
$BR
\{ans_rule(60)\}
$PAR

Now suppose that the corridors are $c feet high, and you are allowed
to tilt the pipe vertically while maneuvering around the corner.
Then the maximal length of pipe which will fit is:
$BR
\{ans_rule(65)\}
END_TEXT

$ans1 = "$a*sec(t)+$b/sin(t)";
$d = ($b/$a)**(2/3);
$ans2 = ($b/$a)**(1/3);
$ans3 = "MIN";
$ans4 = $a*sqrt(1+$d) + $b*sqrt(1+1/$d);
$ans5 = sqrt($ans4**2+$c**2);

&ANS(function_cmp($ans1,"t"));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans2));
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans3));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans4));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans5));

ENDDOCUMENT();
